pgTitle: List of Scheduled prehistoric Monuments in Ceredigion

rows.text:
{{coord|52.5027|-3.9153|name=Ffridd Newydd, Stone Circle c.600m NW of|region:GB_type:landmark}},
SN700911
Some 33 stones set in a circle {{convert|19|m|ft}} across on exposed moorland, east of Tal-y-bont, near Fridd Newydd. Also called Cylch Derwyddol and Moel Llyn, it was first noted in 1847.

{{coord|52.4457|-3.8325|name=Cairn Circle 400m SW of Lle'r Neuaddau|region:GB_type:landmark}},
SN755846
Carn Fawr, with views to Cadair Idris
Excavated in 1937, An inhumation coffin and food vessels (now in the National Museum of Wales) are from early Bronze Age. 600 years later, a cremation burial had alo been made.
